    </div></td><td width="32">Â </td></tr><tr><td valign="top"><div class="es-jasper-simpleCalendar" baseurl="/lkml/"></div><div class="threadlist">Messages in this thread</div><ul class="threadlist"><li class="root"><a href="/lkml/1997/7/13/26">First message in thread</a></li><li><a href="/lkml/1997/7/13/26">Linus Torvalds</a><ul><li class="origin"><a href="">Linus Torvalds</a></li></ul></li></ul></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerl.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="/" /></td><td class="c" rowspan="2" valign="top" style="padding-top: 1em"><table><tr><td colspan="2"><!--BuySellAds Zone Code--><div id="bsap_1297613" class="bsarocks bsap_5aa49c00cc06c882289a1dd6a5e50b62"></div><!--End BuySellAds Zone Code--></td></tr><tr><td><table><tr><td class="lp">Date</td><td class="rp" itemprop="datePublished">Sat, 12 Jul 1997 17:22:27 -0700 (PDT)</td></tr><tr><td class="lp">From</td><td class="rp" itemprop="author">Linus Torvalds &lt;&gt;</td></tr><tr><td class="lp">Subject</td><td class="rp" itemprop="name">Re: New pre-patch..</td></tr></table></td><td><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></td></tr></table><pre itemprop="articleBody"><br /><br />On Sat, 12 Jul 1997, Linus Torvalds wrote:<br />&gt;<br />&gt; Ok, I made yet another pre-patch, and this time it actually does roughly<br />&gt; what it should do.<br /><br />Never mind, as David already claimed I'm batting a 1,000 today. The<br />pre-patch actually mostly works, but the try_to_free function tries to<br />free the _first_ entry on the LRU list rather than the last one, and<br />obviously the first entry is almost always likely to not be freeable at<br />all (because we put anything that has its inode in use at the beginning of<br />the list). <br /><br />So not only does it almost never free anything, but because of that it<br />tends to never do an "iput()", so your filesystem fills up with undead<br />files when you delete them. <br /><br />Simple fix: change the "dentry_unused.next" to a "dentry_unused.prev" in<br />try_free_dentries(). That should at least make it work the way I<br />_intended_ it should work. Whether that makes it any more usable I don't<br />know... <br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
